Dear Hiring Team, 

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the Founding Engineer position with FOUND. I bring over three years of professional experience in production-grade AI systems, multi-agent orchestration, and full-stack development, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade agentic AI systems that directly reflect the technical depth this position demands. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I architected a production-grade multi-agent orchestration system using LangChain and LangGraph that enables concurrent tool execution across 1,000+ endpoints, translating natural-language intents into safe, validated tool calls for end-to-end automated workflows. I owned the complete AI pipeline from data ingestion through retrieval, grounding, and orchestration to output, implementing evaluation frameworks and quality loops using Langfuse and LangSmith for tracing, structured logs, and quality measurement. Through developing evaluation benchmarks and optimizing agent concurrency and prompt routing, I reduced latency by 60% and LLM costs by 50% in production — demonstrating the kind of systems-level thinking and operational rigor required to design and ship agentic AI systems that transform workflows at scale. Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I built a production-grade RAG pipeline using LangChain and PostgreSQL vector store, implementing retrieval and grounding over documentation to reduce ticket resolution time by 20%. I also designed cloud-agnostic data ingestion infrastructure using Python, PostgreSQL, and Redis that handles file operations across Google Cloud Storage, S3, and MinIO, giving me direct experience working with messy, real-world data and distributed systems. Together, these roles have prepared me to own end-to-end AI pipelines and contribute meaningfully to FOUND's core engineering responsibilities.

My academic research experience has given me a rigorous foundation in model development, GPU-accelerated computing, and technical communication — skills that translate directly into the engineering discipline and collaborative culture this team values. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I conducted research on StyleGAN and Stable Diffusion for fashion design generation, managing the full model development lifecycle from data preparation through training on an HPC cluster using CUDA, PyTorch, and LORA fine-tuning. I built model inference infrastructure using vLLM and deployed via Hugging Face, ensuring production-grade model serving. Beyond building the systems myself, I led workshops on GPU programming with CUDA and Mojo, and on building AI Agents with LangChain, LangGraph, and LangSmith for 50+ students. Designing and delivering those sessions required me to break down complex technical concepts clearly and accessibly — directly mirroring the technical communication and knowledge-sharing responsibilities central to a founding engineer role. This experience has shaped me into an engineer who builds with rigor and communicates with clarity, both of which I would bring to FOUND's mission.

I have always been passionate about building agentic AI systems that operate autonomously in complex, real-world environments and envision myself contributing my talent to the furthering of transforming workflows at scale through production-grade AI. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

